# apidiff baselines are gob-encoded binary blobs (golang.org/x/exp/cmd/apidiff
# -w). They are not human-readable; treat as binary so git skips bogus text
# diffs. A baseline changing in a PR is the review signal that the public API
# moved — the readable change is the accompanying source diff. See
# docs/stability.md and api/regen.sh.
api/*.api binary
